# PUBG Mobile Sentiment Analysis — Major Enhancement

Comprehensive overhaul of the dashboard covering UX, model accuracy, multi-language support, export, scraper improvements, and code structure.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Multi-language scope**: The plan implements EN/ID language toggle for the UI labels only. The NLP preprocessing (stemming, slang normalization, stopwords) will remain Indonesian-focused since the reviews are in Bahasa Indonesia. Should we also add English NLP preprocessing for English reviews?

> [!WARNING]
> **PDF export** requires an additional dependency (`fpdf2`). This will be added to `requirements.txt`.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. New File Structure

Current flat structure → organized into modules:

```
├── app.py                  # Main dashboard (refactored)
├── config/
│   └── languages.py        # [NEW] EN/ID translation dictionaries
├── scraper.py              # Enhanced scraper
├── preprocessing.py        # Improved preprocessing
├── model.py                # Improved model
├── utils/
│   └── export.py           # [NEW] CSV/PDF export utilities
├── data/
│   ├── slang_dict.json     # Expanded slang dictionary
│   ├── stopwords_id.txt
│   └── reviews_pubg.csv
├── models/
├── requirements.txt        # Updated
└── README.md
```

---

### 2. Disable Buttons During Processing (Item #1)

#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///c:/Experience/octalectzz/analisis-sentimen-pubg-mobile/app.py)

- Add `st.session_state.is_processing = False` to session state init
- Set it to `True` at the start of training/scraping, `False` at end
- Use `disabled=st.session_state.is_processing` on all buttons (`btn_train`, `btn_compare`, scrape button, predict button)

