### 6. Export to CSV and PDF (Item #6)

#### [NEW] [export.py](file:///c:/Experience/octalectzz/analisis-sentimen-pubg-mobile/utils/export.py)

- `export_csv(df)` → returns CSV bytes for `st.download_button`
- `export_pdf(df, model_result)` → generates PDF report with:
  - Summary statistics
  - Sentiment distribution table
  - Model metrics (accuracy, precision, recall, F1)
  - Uses `fpdf2` library

#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///c:/Experience/octalectzz/analisis-sentimen-pubg-mobile/app.py)

- Add export buttons in Tab 1 (data) and Tab 3 (model evaluation)
- `st.download_button` for CSV and PDF

#### [MODIFY] [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Experience/octalectzz/analisis-sentimen-pubg-mobile/requirements.txt)

- Add `fpdf2` and `requests`

